<section id="Adding_Database_Credentials_for_Data_Collection" remap="TID_19416">
	<title>Adding Database Credentials for Data Collection</title>
	<para>
		After creating the new user, add its credentials to the settings for the provider.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Add Database Credentials for Data Collection</title> 
		<!--step>
			<para>
				Log in to the console.
			</para>
		</step-->
		<step>
			<para>
				From <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>Providers</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, click a provider to update its settings.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Configuration)</guibutton>, and then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1851.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Edit this Provider)</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In the <guilabel>Credentials</guilabel> area, click <guimenuitem>C &amp; U Database</guimenuitem>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Type in the credentials for the new database user you created.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Finally, restart the capacity and utilization data collector. For more information, see <ulink url="https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_CloudForms/3.2/html/Settings_and_Operations_Guide/index.html">CloudForms Management Engine Settings and Operations Guide</ulink>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>